                "id": "introduction",
                "title": "Introduction",
                "content": "<p>The rise of no-code and low-code development platforms has revolutionized the way businesses and individuals build software. These tools enable users with little to no programming knowledge to create functional applications quickly. However, traditional coding and programming still remain the foundation of robust, scalable, and highly customizable applications.</p><p>In this article, we’ll dive deep into the differences between no-code/low-code and coding, highlighting their pros, cons, limitations, and when each approach is the best choice. While no-code and low-code solutions provide convenience, coding and programming remain the superior approach for long-term success in software development.</p>"
