                "id": "what-is-no-code-low-code",
                "title": "What is No-Code/Low-Code Development?",
                "content": "<h3>No-Code Development</h3><p>No-code platforms are designed for users with zero programming knowledge. These platforms offer a visual drag-and-drop interface, allowing users to create applications without writing a single line of code.</p><h3>Low-Code Development</h3><p>Low-code platforms still provide visual development tools but allow for some level of coding for additional customization. Developers can write scripts or integrate APIs to extend functionality.</p><p><strong>Key Features of No-Code/Low-Code Platforms:</strong></p><ul><li>Drag-and-drop UI components</li><li>Pre-built templates and integrations</li><li>Workflow automation capabilities</li><li>Built-in database and backend solutions</li><li>Limited ability to write custom scripts (for low-code)</li></ul>"
