                "id": "pros-cons",
                "title": "Pros and Cons",
                "content": "<h3>No-Code/Low-Code Pros</h3><ul><li>✔ Fast development and deployment.</li><li>✔ Accessible to non-developers.</li><li>✔ Good for small-scale applications.</li><li>✔ Reduces initial development costs.</li></ul><h3>No-Code/Low-Code Cons</h3><ul><li>✘ Limited customization and flexibility.</li><li>✘ Security risks and data dependency on platforms.</li><li>✘ Not suitable for large-scale applications.</li><li>✘ Can become expensive with platform fees.</li></ul><h3>Coding and Programming Pros</h3><ul><li>✔ Complete control over functionality.</li><li>✔ Fully scalable for future growth.</li><li>✔ Strong security and data ownership.</li><li>✔ No long-term dependency on third-party platforms.</li></ul><h3>Coding and Programming Cons</h3><ul><li>✘ Requires skilled developers.</li><li>✘ Longer development time.</li><li>✘ Higher initial investment.</li></ul>"
